Class AbstractCashFlow.Result

  • net.corda.finance.flows.AbstractCashFlow.Result
  • Enclosing class:
    AbstractCashFlow<T>

    public static class AbstractCashFlow.Result

    Combined signed transaction and identity lookup map, which is the resulting data from regular cash flows. Specialised flows for unit tests differ from this.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Result

        public Result(@NotNull
              SignedTransaction stx,
              @Nullable
              AbstractParty recipient)

        Combined signed transaction and identity lookup map, which is the resulting data from regular cash flows. Specialised flows for unit tests differ from this.

        Parameters:
        stx - the signed transaction.
        recipient - the identity used for the other side of the transaction, where applicable (i.e. this isnull for exit transactions). For anonymous transactions this is the confidential identity generated for thetransaction, otherwise this is the well known identity.
